1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:02,080
You didn't do this, you wouldn't, right?

2
00:00:03,840 --> 00:00:05,160
Tell me!

3
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:07,439
Speak.

4
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:09,199
You wouldn't do this.

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,240
Is that really what you think?

6
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:15,280
You keep telling me I'm a Karahan, right?

7
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:17,440
They did this to a Karahan!

8
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:19,800
Cemal, talk to the lawyer.

9
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:23,919
Have him get a broadcast
ban on Mercan's pictures.

10
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:26,400
Have him destroy all of them, if possible.

11
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,520
Okay, I'm on it. Don't you worry.

12
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:33,640
You posted the pictures online, didn't you?

13
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:35,320
Yes, I did.

14
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:37,480
How could you cause such an embarrassment?

15
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:40,760
I'm not the one who caused
this embarrassment but that little

16
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,879
snake who keeps forgetting
she's married and playing around.

17
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,400
Mom!

18
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,040
Hello, Mercan.

19
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:48,920
Another article has just dropped.

20
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,680
"Black swan
Mercan Karahan, is she an unwanted bride?"

21
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,880
"They're saying Mercan
and Ateş Karahan will get divorced soon."

22
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,840
Your mask of innocence has finally fallen.

23
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:01,840
You did this.

24
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:05,880
Why are you so evil, why do you hate me so
much?

25
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,960
Because you deserve it.

26
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:12,000
A shameless and depraved woman like

27
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:14,560
yourself deserves so much worse.

28
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:24,520
This was supposed to be a family portrait.

29
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,840
We're together as a family.

30
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,440
Everyone got the message.

31
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,160
There’s nothing left to worry about.

32
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,680
Thank you for standing by me.

33
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,520
I’ve never felt this bad before.

34
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,680
Even if I said otherwise,

35
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,480
I honestly thought I wouldn’t get through
it…

36
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:29,480
You face everything,

37
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:34,480
but when they attack
your honor, you just want to run and hide.

38
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,240
I guess that’s our fragile side…

39
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:41,040
or at least mine.

40
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,640
I felt like my wings were suddenly broken.

41
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,760
I’ll always be by your side.

42
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,240
You’re stronger than you think.

43
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,200
You can face anything.

44
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:08,440
And when you can’t, I’m here.

45
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,920
I’ll be your wings.

46
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,720
I mean… I’m here.

47
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,920
Don’t worry.

48
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:31,080
I’m sorry I blamed you about those photos.

49
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,440
When you’re angry, your
mind goes everywhere.

50
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,600
I know that well.

51
00:04:56,600 --> 00:05:00,240
I think what hurt me most was your silence.

52
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,520
And what hurt me was you blaming me.

53
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,120
Oh, so you’re cashing in your drama rights
already.

54
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,400
Opportunity came knocking. Why wouldn’t I
use it?

55
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,240
You could let it slide just once.

56
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,840
Moments like this shouldn’t go to waste.

57
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,040
You’ve always been there for me.

58
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,880
In my hardest moments, it was always you.

59
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,600
I know that.

60
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,400
And I always will be.

61
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,840
Why are you doing all this?

62
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,520
… And me…

63
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,720
why am I getting swept up in you?

64
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,440
Yeah, Fatih, listening.

65
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,280
Haydar figured us out, bro.

66
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,880
He came after me. He wanted info about you.

67
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,760
I wasn’t gonna
talk... even if he shot me, I wouldn’t...

68
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,880
but he threatened my family.

69
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,920
I told him you had a brother who died.

70
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:28,840
I’m sorry,
bro. Give me whatever punishment you want.

71
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,520
What punishment, Fatih?

72
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,600
Are you okay? You’re not hurt, right?

73
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:40,520
Okay, take your family and go back home for
a while.

74
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,280
If you need anything, call me.

75
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,240
I’ll protect you and your family.

76
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,080
Talk to you later.

77
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,800
Hello, Cemal.

78
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,280
Get a few men to watch over Fatih.

79
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,440
We don’t leave our brothers behind.

80
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:12,680
And the ones who
betray our brothers don’t walk away free.

81
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,040
I’m on it, don’t worry.

82
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,280
Okay, let’s find him a job too.

83
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,200
Something related to this work.

84
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,680
If I had the chance, I wouldn’t
let that girl breathe for a second.

85
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,040
Look how she jumped into our photo.

86
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,760
Ateş did that to clear Mercan’s name.

87
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,960
And to teach us a lesson.

88
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:48,000
Everything we did went
straight to the trash.

89
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:50,840
And Mercan was all too happy about it.

90
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:54,600
She never misses a chance to stick to Ateş.

91
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,720
I mean, who is she to not want him?

92
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,800
Ateş gave her way too much space.

93
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,800
He made her forget her place.

94
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,600
I’m losing my mind.

95
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,960
Whatever we do, it doesn’t work.

96
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:14,800
Everything just brings them
closer. They’re practically glued together.

97
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,520
It’s not that easy to sway Ateş.

98
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:23,080
His heart has thick, solid walls…

99
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,320
Maybe Mercan cracked one.

100
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:30,000
But we can seal that crack.

101
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,160
Don't worry.

102
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,720
We just need the right moves.

103
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:41,240
We need to
change direction and focus on Mercan.

104
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,880
In other words, she needs to believe
Ateş is bad.

105
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,400
And Mercan is the only obstacle.

106
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:51,320
We need to get rid of her.

107
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,600
Ateş?

108
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,800
Yes, Yaşar?

109
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:14,680
Mrs. Mercan, sorry to bother you this late…

110
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,120
No, please, go ahead.

111
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:21,640
I didn’t get a reply
to my email, so I wanted to remind you...

112
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,880
the deadline for the presentation is in
two days.

113
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,840
We definitely need to
finish it by tomorrow.

114
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:30,920
Oh God… I completely forgot.

115
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,520
Please forgive me.

116
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:37,160
Um... well... send out a meeting notice for
tomorrow.

117
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,200
Got it, Mrs. Mercan.

118
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,640
Alright. See you then.

119
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,440
Mrs. Müzeyyen, please...

120
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,680
You’re comfortable now
because Ateş is right next to you.

121
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:03,800
But I guess no one taught you to stay away
from him.

122
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,120
Then again, with parents like yours,

123
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,600
what
could you have learned besides being trash…

124
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,480
Please stop insulting me.

125
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,800
Ateş will kick you out soon enough.

126
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,360
Don’t say I didn’t warn you.

127
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,120
Be ready for anything.

128
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:21,160
If you mean the divorce, I already know.

129
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,920
Please stop coming after me.

130
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,120
What’s going on here?

131
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:39,560
I’m warning the wife you play house with.

132
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:45,520
Even if your marriage is
fake, her meeting with Nezir isn’t right.

133
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,680
She needs to get herself together.

134
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,120
Müzeyyen Mother!

135
00:10:56,720 --> 00:11:00,560
If something
needs to be said to my wife, I’ll say it.

136
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,360
No one else.

137
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:11,240
And Mercan knows exactly how to behave.

138
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,040
Don’t worry.

139
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,960
Don’t fight with your family because of me.

140
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,440
I can handle it.

141
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,880
I know you can.

142
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,720
But I wanted to say it anyway.

143
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,320
Thank you, really…

144
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:45,240
but I can endure
it... at least until the divorce.

145
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,320
They’ll always be with you.

146
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,960
They’ll always be in your life.

147
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,040
But I won’t be here tomorrow.

148
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,160
If that’s what you think.

149
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,880
Let's get to the main subject.

150
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:20,720
Yaşar called.

151
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,440
The deadline for
the Cultural Center in Italy is almost up.

152
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,120
I asked for a meeting at the office.

153
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:29,560
We need to prepare as soon as possible.

154
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:32,400
I’ll look over things tonight…

155
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:35,080
I had already sent them the starter.

156
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:37,160
I don't understand why
they requested it again.

157
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:40,440
They’re suddenly
trying to rush everything. I don’t get it.

158
00:12:57,720 --> 00:13:00,000
Mercan. Come on, wake up.

159
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,600
But you need to wake up.

160
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,640
I’m sleeping.

161
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:13,960
Mercan, get up.

162
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:21,920
Can you be quiet? I’m sleeping.

163
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,920
But
if I don’t wake you, you’ll get mad at me.

164
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,680
I won’t. Promise.

165
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,680
Okay then. I’m heading to the office.

166
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,800
Mm‑hmm.

167
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,400
We’ll start working on
the Italy presentation with the team.

168
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,360
Good morning.

169
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,280
Good morning.

170
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:13,120
What? What time is it? Why didn’t you wake
me?

171
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,720
I’ve been trying for five minutes.

172
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,440
I just wanted to take a quick look at what
we could do.

173
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,720
I must have fallen asleep.

174
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,400
And I scheduled the meeting. We’re late.

175
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,360
We’re not late.

176
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,880
Sit and calm down.

177
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:40,920
Okay, I’ll get ready.
Don’t go anywhere. We’re going together.

178
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:44,240
Where are my slippers?

179
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:46,320
Just sit down here.

180
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,120
What are you doing? I need to get ready.

181
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,640
I’m helping you.

182
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,680
Calm down.

183
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:10,120
Okay, thank you.

184
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,120
Now
that you’re calmer, you can go get ready.

185
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,840
I'll get ready and be back. Wait for me.

186
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,480
I will.

187
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,960
I'll be back right away. Wait.

188
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,560
They'll always be with you.

189
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:59,040
They'll be in your life.

190
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,000
But I won't be here tomorrow.

191
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,920
I wish you could stay with me forever.

192
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,640
What am I going to do with this girl?

193
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:26,320
She’s clearly lost her mind.

194
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:29,080
God, give me guidance.

195
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:33,840
And don’t forget
my daughter. Obviously she's lost her mind.

196
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:39,240
I swear, I’m bursting. I'm fed up.

197
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:42,120
I’m at a loss. What a mess.

198
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,400
Please, Malik. Let’s leave this place..

199
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,760
Let’s get married and be happy. Huh?

200
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:59,480
My Çiçek,

201
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:02,080
Listen. If we
get married without your family’s blessing,

202
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,080
none of us will be happy, my love.

203
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,640
Misery won’t leave us alone.

204
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:11,440
It never
leaves a place without destroying it first.

205
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,960
I know your heart.

206
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:19,080
You can’t be
happy when the people you love are hurting.

207
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:24,320
And I can’t be happy when you’re hurting.

208
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:27,720
Also Binnaz aunt welcomed me to her table.

209
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,080
She’s done so much for me.

210
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:33,120
Given all that, I can’t do something like
this to her.

211
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:38,680
Çiçek, we’ll be patient and understanding.

212
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,360
Then everything will fall into place.

213
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,600
God is with those who love.

214
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,760
He’ll open a path for us.

215
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,440
You’re right, Malik.

216
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,480
You’re right about everything.

217
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:02,480
I’m so lucky to have
someone this thoughtful.

218
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,360
I just wish my parents could see this.

219
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,280
Maybe then they’d see us differently.

220
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:12,360
They will, Çiçek. They will.

221
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:14,240
They’ll understand eventually.

222
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,960
Time is the only thing we need.

223
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:24,720
He’s an outsider, but he’s honorable.

224
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,000
So what do I do now…

225
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,880
The more I see his kindness,

226
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,520
the more I question everything I thought I
knew.

227
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:36,920
What am I going to do now?

228
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:41,720
Which path is right? Which one hurts less?

229
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,440
God, help me…

230
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:47,800
If only I had someone
by my side to help me,

231
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:51,240
a true companion
who’d sit with me and share my troubles…

232
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,760
I have no one to talk to.

233
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:54,600
So, Binnaz…

234
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,520
it’s all on you.

235
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:01,800
I’m in the hardest situation of my life.

236
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,320
Talking to yourself again, mom?

237
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:15,160
Mom,
you’ve started talking to yourself again.

238
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,240
Who were you thinking about?

239
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:22,440
You’re all I’ve got. Who else?

240
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:26,840
I know what’s bothering you…

241
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,440
I know it.

242
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,360
It’s Çiçek. Right?

243
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,560
Çiçek is bothering you.

244
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:42,280
Don’t be harsh with her, son.

245
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,720
I'm afraid she’s going
to drift even further away from us.

246
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,280
Don't do it. Okay?

247
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,280
I won’t, don’t worry, mom.

248
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,160
I’ve only got one sister.

249
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:57,800
Seriously, I just want
her happy. That’s all.

250
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:01,120
And don’t stress yourself, mom.

251
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,320
I'm not
going to be harsh on her. Don't worry, huh?

252
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,800
I'm here.

253
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,160
Mother...

254
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,520
My lion-hearted son.

255
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,520
Would you like some tea?

256
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,440
Let's have.

257
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:36,640
We have very little time
left for the art center.

258
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,640
That’s a disadvantage.

259
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,960
But I know we also have a great team,

260
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,280
and that’s our biggest advantage.

261
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:52,800
I’m sure we’ll get through this together.

262
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,320
Yes, there’s nothing
this team can’t finish.

263
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,480
We’ve done it before, you know.

264
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,760
The hotel project.

265
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,160
Exactly.

266
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,840
What a job that was. We
were literally racing against seconds.

267
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,240
But we managed.

268
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,760
And now we’re even stronger.

269
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,080
Everyone’s an expert, everyone’s motivated.

270
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:21,120
What matters
is coordination and sharing the workload…

271
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:31,840
So there was a meeting…

272
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:34,160
Why wasn’t I invited?

273
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,760
Nezir, this is a project-specific meeting.

274
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:43,040
So, could you please give us some space?

275
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:15,240
Now... Burak will prepare the cost reports.

276
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,920
Demet will handle the
interior design details.

277
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:20,240
All information will be collected by Yaşar.

278
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:26,360
Zahide, you work with Yaşar.

279
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,200
Finalize the document together.

280
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:32,480
Uh‑huh.

281
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,360
Let’s wrap this up quickly.

282
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,840
Alright then… let’s get to work.

283
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:44,680
Cool. Then I'll find something to
keep me busy.

284
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:47,760
Good luck.

285
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,280
You impress the employees.

286
00:22:58,360 --> 00:22:59,640
You’re not bad yourself.

287
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,720
Thanks.

288
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,320
It’s going to be a long night.

289
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:08,000
And a very exhausting one.

290
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:10,880
Do you think we can win?

291
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,120
There’s
one thing I’ve learned these past months.

292
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:20,520
There’s nothing
you can’t do once you set your mind to it.

293
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,880
Really?

294
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,240
Really.

295
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:34,560
I’m heading to my office.

296
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,280
Grab the documents and
come there. We’ll work in my office.

297
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,720
We can work in mine too.

298
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:42,720
Oh come on… why are you arguing now?

299
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,160
I’m not arguing.

300
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,720
We’re racing against time. Look, we already
lost five minutes.

301
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:52,440
Okay, you’re right.

302
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,440
Just this once, I won’t argue.

303
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:59,720
Um, I’ll grab my
documents and my laptop and come.

304
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,440
Come on, I'll be waiting.

305
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:20,360
Well,
well… where’s all this money coming from?

306
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:22,400
Did you find a treasure?

307
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:27,680
We don’t die that easily, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

308
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:30,880
We’re not that lucky.

309
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,520
We didn’t get
here overnight unlike some people.

310
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,400
That part we know.

311
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:42,000
We also saw how many people you hurt along
the way.

312
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:49,640
The lives you stepped
on, the ones you took…

313
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,680
How you sleep at night is beyond me.

314
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,040
That's a lie.

315
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,080
All lies and slander.

316
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,320
You know it’s not.

317
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:03,440
You know exactly
what kind of man your husband is.

318
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:10,520
And you still lived, laughed,
ate, drank, traveled, enjoyed life.

319
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,240
Shame.

320
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:14,400
How could you sleep peacefully...

321
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:16,520
while so many deaths
are on your conscience?

322
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:19,520
My conscience is clear.

323
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:21,680
I sleep just fine.

324
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:28,320
Once someone loses their shame, anything is
possible.

325
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:33,200
Stop dodging and tell me... how did you buy
all that?

326
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:42,160
Mrs. Müzeyyen! It’s my money.

327
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,640
I’ll spend it however I want.

328
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,800
It’s none of your business.

329
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:55,840
Whatever she's up to, it’ll come out soon
enough.

330
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:19,840
I see you’re getting
a little too comfortable playing the wife,

331
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,040
fake bride.

332
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:25,360
Or should I say the black swan.

333
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:31,880
He didn’t put you in that family photo for
you.

334
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:34,560
He did it for us.

335
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:40,120
To save our name, not yours.

336
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:43,200
Don’t get your hopes up for nothing…

337
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:50,800
You can only get close
to Ateş as part of a game.

338
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:52,760
You don’t exist in reality.

339
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:58,840
Okay, I don’t exist.

340
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,400
Only you do.

341
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,600
You the most.

342
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,560
Agreed?

343
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,440
Now leave my room…

344
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,880
The days will pass quickly.

345
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:17,680
Once you’re divorced, Ateş
will be nothing but a dream to you.

346
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:27,840
You’ll
be alone with your troubles and your filth.

347
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:32,640
And
we’ll be together again, just like before.

348
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,960
You don’t like me, I get it.

349
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:42,200
But I’m not bothering
you. Why are you bothering me?

350
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,920
Oh wait, I know.

351
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,440
You’re...

352
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,600
that jealous girl from class, aren’t you?

353
00:27:55,520 --> 00:27:59,960
Insecure, petty, spoiled.

354
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,640
I thought you’d grow out of it.

355
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,120
Turns out you either never grew up,

356
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,800
or you grew up but stayed that girl.

357
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,760
Which is worse, you decide.

358
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:18,760
Now you can leave my office. I’m working.

359
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:34,960
Patience.

360
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:55,480
Zehra… why aren’t you answering my calls?

361
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,360
You’re not replying to my messages either…

362
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:01,040
Why should I? Huh?

363
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:02,960
You talk to people worth talking to.

364
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,640
Zehra… that’s harsh.

365
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,160
Oh please.

366
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,280
Do you want to know what's on my mind.

367
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:25,040
Turns out you were just playing with me.

368
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,800
Zehra, where are you getting this from?

369
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,360
I told you, that’s not true.

370
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:36,080
Why won’t you believe me, love?

371
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,520
How could you think that?

372
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,160
Oh, it’s possible.

373
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:43,840
I figured it out.

374
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:49,080
God give me patience.

375
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:51,360
But you never believe me.

376
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,160
You never listen to me, my sultan.

377
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:56,360
Move, Berat. I’m working.

378
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:59,400
I don’t
have time for nonsense or for useless men.

379
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,840
Um... let me help…

380
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:06,320
But take that back.

381
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,400
Calling me useless is too much.

382
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,640
Okay, okay...

383
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,720
Don’t take it back.

384
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,560
Let me carry these.

385
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,240
Like this? Right? Just a minute.

386
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,280
Alright… there you are…

387
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:28,440
No, Berat. Move out of the way. Let go.

388
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,800
But… I… Zehra…

389
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,600
… I don’t have bad intentions.

390
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:35,760
I’m serious. There
isn’t even a drop of bad intention in me.

391
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,280
Zehra… I’m thinking… maybe…

392
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:41,880
Let’s meet tonight and talk properly

393
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,760
at a place with a lake view. Shall we?

394
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,480
Hmm.

395
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,240
No.

396
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:53,720
Why not?

397
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,480
Never, Berat.

398
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:59,040
Let’s stop seeing each other. Okay? Here.
Take it.

399
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:00,920
Keep being like this.

400
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:14,600
Just
once… can something in my life go right…

401
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:19,440
Man…

402
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,840
What do you want?

403
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:41,360
You pulled all the qualified workers
into your own project.

404
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:44,600
There’s no one left for the plaza project.

405
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:46,960
Let me remind you... we’re partners.

406
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:51,160
How could I forget such
a massive stupidity…

407
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:56,480
I read the plaza reports.

408
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,480
Everything’s going fine.

409
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:01,000
You can continue with the staff you have.

410
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:07,080
I decide who works
where… just like I decide everything else.

411
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,640
If you don’t like it,

412
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:13,080
you can leave the partnership right now.

413
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,560
It doesn’t work like that.

414
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,080
I’m not leaving…

415
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:20,160
You’ll see me every day.

416
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:29,800
A man wants a real enemy standing in front
of him.

417
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:33,440
Might be hard for you,

418
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:38,800
but try being honorable for once and fight
like a man.

419
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:43,080
If you show your real face, I’d gladly do
that.

420
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,280
Look closely...

421
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:50,520
this is my one and only real face.

422
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,880
In fact, you should know it by heart...

423
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:57,080
since
you see it in your nightmares all the time.

424
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:02,920
And you’ll keep seeing it.

425
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:54,240
So beautiful…

426
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,360
Come in.

427
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:10,240
I
Thought you might be tired after shopping.

428
00:34:10,640 --> 00:34:12,560
Bless you, dear. This is perfect.

429
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:14,240
Leave it there…

430
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:26,200
So, what's going on?

431
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:32,000
They were upset
that Mrs. Mercan joined the family photo…

432
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:42,600
Oh, I did some shopping today.

433
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:48,040
I bought
this but I already have something similar.

434
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:52,280
It would look great on you.

435
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,440
The color is perfect for you.

436
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:57,800
Here, take it…

437
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:00,120
Really?

438
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:07,120
Thank you so much, Mrs. Nermin!

439
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:15,880
So tell me, how upset was Müzeyyen?

440
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:19,240
Very. She was so
surprised. I’ve never seen her like that.

441
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:21,480
Why is she surprised?

442
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,760
Isn’t my daughter the bride?

443
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:29,600
Oh…

444
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:35,040
Look… Look, I like you.

445
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,760
You’re smart and capable.

446
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:41,360
From now
on, if you ever need anything, come to me.

447
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:43,080
We’ll sort it out.

448
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,400
If you’ll excuse me…

449
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:59,600
HAYDAR: What’s she doing here? Don’t let
her in too much.

450
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:03,480
I’m slowly turning her into a Trojan horse.

451
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:06,360
She’ll be useful one day.

452
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:16,280
HAYDAR: You know what?
You’re a terrible woman.

453
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:17,800
Terrible…

454
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,320
Good.

455
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:23,520
Actually, the
best Trojan horse is already in our hands…

456
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:26,040
Ateş is in love with Mercan.

457
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:30,080
What love, woman? Don’t drive me crazy!

458
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,400
You spoke nonsense like this before.

459
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:35,520
Impossible. Not in this lifetime!

460
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:37,360
Not even if the world ended.

461
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:40,160
Say impossible all you want…

462
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:44,280
Love makes the impossible possible.

463
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:46,840
You’ll be shocked.

464
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,840
Enough, Nermin! Stop it.

465
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:52,080
As long as I’m here, no one dares.

466
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:53,760
And don’t ever say that again.

467
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,720
God forbid.

468
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,120
There should be a universal aesthetic,

469
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:13,120
but we shouldn’t
ignore local motifs either.

470
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,840
Yes… um…

471
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,720
If we bring those two together in harmony,

472
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:21,000
the project’s chances increase a lot.

473
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,360
Right. Look…

474
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:26,520
Let us…

475
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:30,560
put the library and workshops on the lower
floor

476
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,840
so they’re easy to reach.

477
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,680
We can place the library here.

478
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:43,680
I love libraries.

479
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:46,680
I can practically smell the books now.

480
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,760
What do you think of this section?

481
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,880
Agreed… um…

482
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,640
Let’s define
the galleries on the upper floor.

483
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,680
And this part for digital art.

484
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,400
Hmm.

485
00:38:02,160 --> 00:38:03,920
That's possible.

486
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:26,720
Um… I drifted off.

487
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,040
I realized our
architectural tastes are similar.

488
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:35,160
Same here. We agreed pretty fast.

489
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,800
Knock on wood.

490
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,280
We’ll be here till morning…

491
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:51,520
The
lemon one is really good. Come on, try it.

492
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:07,280
It is good.

493
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:12,040
I made them.

494
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:15,840
Zero credibility.

495
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:22,560
Smiling suits you.

496
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:26,960
I wish you did it more often.

497
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:39,960
I’ll try.

498
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:47,680
But neither the ghosts of the past

499
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,240
nor the enemies

500
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:55,040
waiting in the future let me.

501
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:10,680
It's Cemal.

502
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:14,240
Turn off your
phone. We’re at camp, remember?

503
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,240
Give it to me…

504
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:20,880
I don’t think so.

505
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:25,040
Come on. Look, I turned mine off.

506
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:28,080
No. I need it.

507
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:33,240
Give me the phone.

508
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,920
No. Leave my phone alone.

509
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,160
Give it to me.

510
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:40,600
-Let go. -Give me the phone.

511
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,160
Give it.

512
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:48,560
Give it to me!

513
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:50,520
–I said give. –Let go.

514
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:51,720
Give it.

515
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,640
How can anyone not fall in love with you?

516
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:03,720
Why do I lose control when I’m near you?

517
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:06,040
Why does everything disappear?

518
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:10,040
Who could resist these eyes?

519
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:21,120
It’s only your eyes I’m drawn to…

520
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:23,520
God, what’s happening to me…

521
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:37,560
-I’ll check on Cemal. -Okay…

522
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:49,680
It’s
always beating… always pounding like this…

523
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,000
Get a grip, Mercan.

524
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,480
Impossible…

525
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:31,600
Fix the data over there too.

526
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:37,080
Okay. I’ll combine
them with what Mrs. Mercan sent.

527
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:40,920
Oh no!

528
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:43,760
How could you do this, Yaşar?

529
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:45,280
"de" should be printed separately.

530
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:48,240
"de"
is written separately when it means "also."

531
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:50,560
What?

532
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:52,880
Never mind, just separate it.

533
00:42:53,600 --> 00:42:55,720
Also, attach those visuals, below.

534
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:59,480
But Zahide, I can’t work like this.

535
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:04,280
I mean… Um…

536
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:08,960
Actually, I can work any
way you want, Ms Zahide…

537
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:14,200
but… maybe if I used a little initiative,
I’d be more… motivated… maybe…

538
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:16,600
Fine. Alright. Go ahead then.

539
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:19,480
You fix the visuals, I’ll handle the data.

540
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:22,720
What perfume is this…

541
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:25,040
are you the scent of heaven or what?

542
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:27,920
It’s driving me crazy.

543
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:30,720
Did you say something?

544
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:33,520
No, no, just working…

545
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:34,920
Hmm…

546
00:43:41,760 --> 00:43:43,920
DEMET: Psst. BURAK: Huh?

547
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:48,880
Without gossip there’s no joy in working.

548
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:51,080
Uh huh.

549
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:59,200
How do I
adjust the screen brightness again, Burak?

550
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:01,200
Let me show you.

551
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:09,520
Here… is this okay?

552
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:14,640
Yes.

553
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:16,640
Okay.

554
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:22,240
I know why
you’re acting like this, but please don’t.

555
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:26,080
Don’t let my brother’s empty threats ruin
our friendship.

556
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:30,640
Your brother’s threats don’t matter, Demet.

557
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:37,080
Anyway… we don’t have time for this now.
Let's focus on those.

558
00:44:52,160 --> 00:44:53,880
Ouch.

559
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,040
Çiçek, wait.

560
00:45:10,120 --> 00:45:12,800
Why are you carrying that heavy stuff? Give
it to me.

561
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:15,800
Why are you carrying something this heavy?

562
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:19,120
Especially when I'm around. I can't accept
that.

563
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:28,600
Thank you, Malik.

564
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:29,920
Of course.

565
00:45:30,200 --> 00:45:31,480
I’m glad you’re here.

566
00:45:31,560 --> 00:45:34,120
You always help me. Whenever
I struggle, you’re right there.

567
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:36,560
Always. It’ll always be like this.

568
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:41,080
Look at him… doing everything.

569
00:45:41,200 --> 00:45:44,280
Carrying the load like a real man.

570
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:46,840
He really loves my daughter.

571
00:45:50,240 --> 00:45:51,640
-See you. -Bye, Malik.

572
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:54,520
See you.

573
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:57,280
♪ My heart is burning, mother… ♪

574
00:45:57,520 --> 00:46:00,320
♪ mother, mother, mother… ♪

575
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:05,280
♪ Burning, mother, mother… ♪

576
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:11,120
♪ Melting, mother, mother, mother… ♪

577
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:13,640
♪ My heart is burning, mother... ♪

578
00:46:13,720 --> 00:46:15,320
Why are you yelling "mother, mother"?

579
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:18,320
♪ Mother. I'm done, Mother. ♪

580
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:21,680
♪ Melting, mother, mother, mother… ♪

581
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:25,800
Oh, God forbid. Son, what’s all this "I’m
burning"? What are you saying?

582
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:29,120
Here, I’m here. What is it?

583
00:46:32,640 --> 00:46:34,040
I’m singing, mom…

584
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:35,680
I'm singing "türkü".

585
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:37,200
God forbid, son.

586
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:39,640
What is this singing "I'm burning, mother?"

587
00:46:39,720 --> 00:46:41,640
People cry "mother" when they’re
in trouble.

588
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:42,880
Are you troubled, son?

589
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:45,200
No, no trouble, Mother.

590
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:47,520
Just messing around.

591
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:50,760
God forbid. He's just "messing around."

592
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:53,560
♪ Melting, mother, mother, mother… ♪

593
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:56,080
God forbid.

594
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:56,880
♪ … mother ♪...

595
00:46:56,960 --> 00:47:00,040
Oh! You almost gave me a heart attack!

596
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:02,720
You’ll be the reason for my death!

597
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:04,320
Don't say that, Mother.

598
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:07,960
♪ God forbid, Mother. ♪

599
00:47:08,040 --> 00:47:09,680
♪ Mother, mother… ♪

600
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:12,000
♪ Mother, mother… ♪

601
00:47:12,640 --> 00:47:14,160
♪ Oh, Mother… ♪

602
00:47:14,360 --> 00:47:15,880
♪ What was my fault? ♪

603
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:17,360
♪ My fault, my fault… ♪

604
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:21,280
♪ I
called you "my rose", my Zehra, my Zehra… ♪

605
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:24,320
♪ I’ll bring your bride to you. ♪

606
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:26,440
♪ Mother, mother… ♪

607
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:28,640
♪ Mother… ♪

608
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:32,680
We sent Fatih and his family home safely.

609
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:35,760
They have guards with them. I’m keeping an
eye on everything.

610
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:40,880
If you’re on it, I don’t worry, brother.

611
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:42,400
Thank you.

612
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:45,280
What are we doing about Haydar?

613
00:47:48,480 --> 00:47:50,160
Clearly he doesn’t have much.

614
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:53,520
If
He did, we’d have heard something by now.

615
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:56,080
But anyhow, we should stay cautious.

616
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:58,280
He won’t let it go.

617
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:01,280
He'll keep investigating.

618
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:04,360
We need to know who he
talks to, where he goes.

619
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:22,240
Why did your face suddenly drop?

620
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:25,680
Here’s my advice to you.

621
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:27,960
Don’t hide your smile or your feelings.

622
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:31,080
Life’s too short. Here
one day, gone the next.

623
00:48:31,520 --> 00:48:33,320
How long will you keep running?

624
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:35,760
As long as I can…

625
00:48:37,400 --> 00:48:42,000
I'll
keep running… until I crash into something.

626
00:48:43,200 --> 00:48:45,360
When it comes to sacrificing for others,

627
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:47,000
you’re always the first to step up.

628
00:48:49,720 --> 00:48:52,240
Just like you did for me before I was shot.

629
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:56,720
You almost died because of me.

630
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:02,520
Fight for
yourself too. Fight for your own happiness.

631
00:49:03,680 --> 00:49:06,360
Listen to your heart for once.

632
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,160
Maybe
fighting for yourself is the hardest thing.

633
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,160
Probably.

634
00:49:15,680 --> 00:49:19,280
But doing the hard thing
is what you’re best at, isn’t it, Ateş?

635
00:49:20,520 --> 00:49:23,560
What’s going on, Cemal?
Did I miss something?

636
00:49:24,680 --> 00:49:26,640
Alright, you’re a man of the heart. Fine.

637
00:49:27,680 --> 00:49:29,760
But you talk like you’ve lived it.

638
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:54,600
No, Ateş.

639
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,920
My wounds are on the body, not the heart.

640
00:49:57,280 --> 00:50:01,840
You know… just things I heard in movies.

641
00:50:02,080 --> 00:50:03,200
I picked it up from there.

642
00:50:04,360 --> 00:50:06,960
Anyway, think about what I said.

643
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,720
In this life, more than friends or enemies,

644
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,600
a person needs their own mercy.

645
00:50:13,840 --> 00:50:16,200
See you later.

646
00:50:43,120 --> 00:50:45,080
We need to do something fast.

647
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:48,200
Ateş and Mercan are glued together.

648
00:50:49,760 --> 00:50:52,600
If the
project succeeds, they’ll get even closer.

649
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:54,680
We have to stop it.

650
00:50:57,200 --> 00:50:58,600
I was thinking the same…

651
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:01,240
I have an idea.

652
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:05,240
I don’t know what you’re planning.

653
00:51:05,560 --> 00:51:07,240
I’m not even sure I want to know.

654
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:11,160
But whatever
you’re planning, make it quick.

655
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:34,760
We’ll choose all building materials
to match the concept.

656
00:51:35,280 --> 00:51:37,680
And the design should
focus on young people.

657
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:39,680
The interior and exterior

658
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:42,920
should encourage creativity,

659
00:51:43,400 --> 00:51:45,480
and it should function as a social space.

660
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:55,160
Ugh. Time is flying.

661
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:56,880
We still have so much to do.

662
00:51:58,120 --> 00:52:01,080
Don’t panic. We’ll make it.

663
00:52:01,200 --> 00:52:02,720
Not at this pace.

664
00:52:04,760 --> 00:52:07,160
Let’s not
cluster all the social areas in one place.

665
00:52:09,680 --> 00:52:11,120
Like this?

666
00:52:12,800 --> 00:52:16,360
Kind of… but this part isn’t good.

667
00:52:20,840 --> 00:52:22,080
I think it’s fine.

668
00:52:23,760 --> 00:52:25,000
No, it’s not.

669
00:52:26,680 --> 00:52:29,160
Don’t argue, let’s fix it. We’re losing
time.

670
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:31,520
But it matches what we discussed…

671
00:52:33,960 --> 00:52:35,360
But it doesn’t work.

672
00:52:36,160 --> 00:52:38,000
How do I say… I want something more…

673
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:41,760
Don’t say anything. Here, you do it.

674
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:44,480
There you go again.

675
00:52:45,520 --> 00:52:47,160
I can only start when you stop talking.

676
00:52:47,720 --> 00:52:49,360
Oh, so I talk too much?

677
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:52,960
That’s what they say about people who don’t
stop once they start.

678
00:52:53,560 --> 00:52:54,840
Is that so. Fine.

679
00:52:55,320 --> 00:52:58,200
You’ll see. I’m not opening my mouth again.

680
00:52:59,160 --> 00:53:02,280
That won’t work. Don’t even try.

681
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:23,320
See? I told you it wouldn’t work.

682
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:26,960
But if you add this part, it will.

683
00:54:01,320 --> 00:54:02,680
The balance looks good.

684
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:05,480
You’re amazing.

685
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:10,720
And me?

686
00:54:17,560 --> 00:54:18,800
You’re amazing too…

687
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:28,040
I mean… your idea was amazing.

688
00:54:32,520 --> 00:54:34,640
But just
so you know, you couldn’t resist talking.

689
00:54:34,720 --> 00:54:36,320
Of course I’m going to talk.

690
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:38,680
How else are we supposed to understand each
other?

691
00:54:41,920 --> 00:54:43,200
Congratulations, Ateş Bey.

692
00:54:45,040 --> 00:54:46,800
Likewise, Mrs. Mercan.

693
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:00,560
Ateş,

694
00:55:01,440 --> 00:55:03,600
let’s go home. It’s late.

695
00:55:03,920 --> 00:55:05,520
Let the staff finish it.

696
00:55:07,040 --> 00:55:08,600
Not that the outcome is even clear.

697
00:55:12,640 --> 00:55:14,520
There’s a lot to do.
I’m here until morning.

698
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:18,520
Come on, let’s go, Aslı.

699
00:55:20,720 --> 00:55:23,160
I don’t want you exhausting yourself like
this.

700
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:24,680
Continue tomorrow.

701
00:55:28,040 --> 00:55:29,960
No need to worry about me.

702
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:32,240
I promised the team I’d work.

703
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:37,960
You
made a promise to us too in the beginning.

704
00:55:41,600 --> 00:55:42,680
Okay, come on, Aslı.

705
00:55:43,720 --> 00:55:46,640
Let’s go. I’ll buy
you that dessert you like on the way home…

706
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:55,960
What promise?

707
00:55:56,240 --> 00:55:58,920
What is she talking about? What promise?

708
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:07,680
Ateş…

709
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:13,080
the power’s out.

710
00:56:13,160 --> 00:56:14,480
I was just thinking about this.

711
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:17,440
She must have something in her mind.

712
00:56:20,720 --> 00:56:22,600
Okay. It’ll probably come back soon.

713
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:26,440
What are we going to do
now? How are we supposed to work?

714
00:56:27,560 --> 00:56:30,200
Cemal, please check the breaker.

715
00:56:30,360 --> 00:56:31,440
Maybe it tripped.

716
00:56:31,520 --> 00:56:33,160
Sure. I'll check it on my way out.

717
00:56:33,240 --> 00:56:35,520
We'll head home from there. Come on, Aslı.

718
00:56:39,680 --> 00:56:41,520
Come on, Aslı. Let's go.

719
00:56:58,160 --> 00:57:00,920
Don’t be scared, it’s just me…

720
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:34,440
What's up?

721
00:57:37,240 --> 00:57:38,520
Zehra, wait! Wait!

722
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:42,320
What are you
doing?! Just listen to me, Zehra!

723
00:57:42,400 --> 00:57:45,040
No need, Berat! Got it?

724
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:47,200
You’re talking nonsense!

725
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:49,880
Just come here, Zehra. Listen to me.

726
00:57:49,960 --> 00:57:52,600
What’s wrong? Why are you flaring up? Calm
down, will you…

727
00:57:52,680 --> 00:57:55,280
I’m not like other girls, okay?

728
00:57:55,440 --> 00:57:58,200
I’m not anyone’s entertainment.
I never was, and I never will be!

729
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:00,480
Wait.

730
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:03,720
I’m not like other men, okay?

731
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:06,440
I’m a man of honor.
I don’t play around with anyone’s heart.

732
00:58:06,560 --> 00:58:08,680
-Oh really? Is that so?! -Yes!

733
00:58:08,760 --> 00:58:11,880
I don’t
want to play with you… I want to marry you!

734
00:58:25,760 --> 00:58:27,240
Berat!

735
00:58:28,560 --> 00:58:30,000
Okay!

736
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:33,440
I accept! I accept! Yes!

737
00:58:33,520 --> 00:58:35,720
Come ask
for my hand from Mrs. Müzeyyen immediately!

738
00:58:35,800 --> 00:58:38,200
Come with your mother, alright?

739
00:58:39,680 --> 00:58:41,480
Uh… my mom…

740
00:58:42,240 --> 00:58:44,000
-Uh‑huh. -Um…

741
00:58:44,520 --> 00:58:46,160
Isn’t that a bit sudden?

742
00:58:46,280 --> 00:58:48,280
Good things happen suddenly, Berat.

743
00:58:48,560 --> 00:58:49,680
-Oh. -Uh‑huh.

744
00:58:50,440 --> 00:58:52,120
Okay, now I have too much work to do.

745
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:53,920
I’ll start preparing right away.

746
00:58:55,920 --> 00:58:57,360
Yes!

747
00:59:00,600 --> 00:59:02,640
Well, looks like she was
eager from the start.

748
00:59:04,120 --> 00:59:05,320
Berat…

749
00:59:15,160 --> 00:59:16,840
Oh, God.

750
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:23,120
Berat, what did you do now?

751
00:59:25,280 --> 00:59:27,920
Thank God.

752
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:31,600
My mother will shoot me.

753
00:59:40,160 --> 00:59:43,600
Okay. But try to fix it immediately. We've
something very important to finish.

754
00:59:44,200 --> 00:59:45,760
Okay.

755
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:59,320
Give me good news.

756
00:59:59,560 --> 01:00:01,520
I spoke with management.

757
01:00:01,960 --> 01:00:04,040
Repairs are still going on.

758
01:00:04,880 --> 01:00:06,280
Just our luck.

759
01:00:06,360 --> 01:00:08,280
And the generator’s acting up.

760
01:00:08,720 --> 01:00:10,360
We can’t activate it either.

761
01:00:11,680 --> 01:00:13,840
So what are we going to
do? How will we finish?

762
01:00:15,600 --> 01:00:17,440
Don’t get pessimistic yet.

763
01:00:18,320 --> 01:00:20,720
We’ll work until the laptops die.

764
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:23,360
Maybe the electricity will be back by then.

765
01:00:23,680 --> 01:00:26,080
If not, we’ll find another solution.

766
01:00:29,080 --> 01:00:30,720
Are you cold?

767
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,800
I’m freezing.

768
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:37,960
The
heating doesn’t work without electricity.

769
01:00:42,520 --> 01:00:44,000
Just stay where you are.

770
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:51,680
Use this for now.

771
01:00:51,800 --> 01:00:53,640
Thanks, but what about you?

772
01:01:02,040 --> 01:01:03,960
I’m fine. Don't worry about me.

773
01:01:06,080 --> 01:01:07,720
Don’t forget what your doctor said.

774
01:01:10,520 --> 01:01:12,400
How could I forget?

775
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:14,640
I’ve dealt with this since childhood.

776
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:20,200
You’re not very
careful with your medication either.

777
01:01:21,840 --> 01:01:23,640
I am.

778
01:01:24,240 --> 01:01:26,120
I have to be for life, anyway.

779
01:01:29,640 --> 01:01:31,720
You must
have gone through difficult things.

780
01:01:33,160 --> 01:01:34,800
It was hard.

781
01:01:36,040 --> 01:01:38,040
My childhood was
half‑lived in hospital rooms,

782
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:41,400
under the smell of medicine.

783
01:01:55,720 --> 01:01:57,240
You were lucky.

784
01:02:00,360 --> 01:02:04,040
I heard finding a compatible donor
takes years.

785
01:02:05,360 --> 01:02:08,160
Yes. I guess I was lucky.

786
01:02:10,800 --> 01:02:12,720
I remember how shocked I was when I learned

787
01:02:12,800 --> 01:02:14,840
I was carrying someone else’s kidney.

788
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:17,480
I even asked
what that person would do without a kidney.

789
01:02:17,760 --> 01:02:19,360
Childish thoughts…

790
01:02:19,960 --> 01:02:22,400
I didn’t know how anything worked.

791
01:02:25,080 --> 01:02:27,920
I read that the risk continues for life.

792
01:02:33,560 --> 01:02:35,360
You should take better care of yourself.

793
01:02:37,480 --> 01:02:39,240
There’s always a risk.

794
01:02:40,560 --> 01:02:43,360
I’m alive because of the person who gave me
their kidney.

795
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:51,760
Every night
before I sleep, I pray for them…

796
01:02:52,800 --> 01:02:54,680
for their peace…

797
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:57,840
But it’s strange

798
01:02:57,920 --> 01:03:00,560
not knowing the name of
the person I owe owe my life to.

799
01:03:04,320 --> 01:03:06,680
I can help you find the person if you like.

800
01:03:07,560 --> 01:03:09,080
Even if you did, it wouldn’t matter.

801
01:03:10,680 --> 01:03:12,400
It was from someone who died.

802
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:31,480
Because I know what it means…

803
01:03:33,160 --> 01:03:34,800
I registered to donate my organs too.

804
01:03:44,960 --> 01:03:48,880
Maybe then, for the first time in my life,

805
01:03:51,840 --> 01:03:53,760
I’ll find real peace…

806
01:04:26,040 --> 01:04:27,640
You’re so innocent.

807
01:04:28,480 --> 01:04:32,880
How did you manage to
live among so much evil all this time?

808
01:04:33,720 --> 01:04:35,600
How did I live so far away from you?

809
01:04:45,000 --> 01:04:47,120
Why am I so affected by you?

810
01:04:48,280 --> 01:04:50,280
Wasn’t it hatred between us?

811
01:04:51,400 --> 01:04:53,240
We went through so many terrible things.

812
01:04:53,760 --> 01:04:55,800
We hurt each other, broke each other.

813
01:04:56,800 --> 01:04:58,160
So what’s happening now?

814
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:00,440
What is that in your eyes?

815
01:05:09,600 --> 01:05:12,200
We got carried away talking.

816
01:05:39,920 --> 01:05:41,360
You’re not cold anymore, right?

817
01:05:44,400 --> 01:05:45,800
No. I'm fine.

818
01:05:46,640 --> 01:05:49,320
Let's get
back to work. We won’t make it otherwise.

819
01:05:56,000 --> 01:05:57,680
Trust me. We’ll make it.

820
01:07:03,600 --> 01:07:04,960
Where’s my necklace?

821
01:07:07,400 --> 01:07:08,920
It's probably here.

822
01:07:12,360 --> 01:07:14,680
I don't understand. Where
did this disappear to?

823
01:07:20,040 --> 01:07:21,440
Not here.

824
01:07:24,160 --> 01:07:25,440
Did someone take it?

825
01:07:26,440 --> 01:07:29,360
No, impossible. Who would dare…

826
01:07:31,440 --> 01:07:32,840
Not here.

827
01:07:34,360 --> 01:07:35,680
Huh!

828
01:07:57,240 --> 01:07:58,840
I must’ve given it to Aslı.

829
01:08:00,160 --> 01:08:02,320
It’s probably in her room. I’ll check…

830
01:08:03,320 --> 01:08:06,040
It’s late. I’ll ask tomorrow.

831
01:08:38,760 --> 01:08:41,440
My battery’s about to die. And yours…

832
01:08:44,440 --> 01:08:46,000
yours too.

833
01:08:46,880 --> 01:08:48,920
We’re not going to make it. Impossible…

834
01:08:58,840 --> 01:09:02,520
I got so caught up in everything lately.

835
01:09:02,760 --> 01:09:04,080
I neglected the work.

836
01:09:04,240 --> 01:09:06,600
Trying to fix it last minute never works…

837
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:09,840
Oh, Mercan, really.

838
01:09:11,640 --> 01:09:13,000
Calm down.

839
01:09:14,080 --> 01:09:15,520
We’ll handle it.

840
01:09:18,640 --> 01:09:21,760
Maybe. Or maybe we won’t.

841
01:09:22,040 --> 01:09:23,960
But
that’s not the problem. The problem is me.

842
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:26,040
I shouldn’t be this affected by everything.

843
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:27,880
I should’ve been stronger.

844
01:09:28,280 --> 01:09:31,200
You blame yourself too fast. Don’t.

845
01:09:32,400 --> 01:09:33,960
I’m at fault too…

846
01:09:34,840 --> 01:09:37,840
You’re dealing with a
thousand things already.

847
01:09:38,360 --> 01:09:40,200
Forgetting something happens.

848
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:44,080
I… no, it’s all my fault.

849
01:09:45,640 --> 01:09:47,800
You forgive everyone else’s mistakes,

850
01:09:48,560 --> 01:09:50,160
but you can’t forgive your own?

851
01:09:52,400 --> 01:09:55,160
I don’t forgive
myself, so I won’t repeat the same mistake.

852
01:09:56,040 --> 01:09:57,640
And you’re any different?

853
01:09:57,800 --> 01:09:59,200
Not as much as you.

854
01:10:00,120 --> 01:10:01,840
Calm down now.

855
01:10:03,400 --> 01:10:06,360
I can’t. I can't.

856
01:10:06,560 --> 01:10:11,440
When the team is so motivated, if we fail…

857
01:10:11,840 --> 01:10:16,080
If I had opened Yaşar’s
email on time, we wouldn’t have lost hours.

858
01:10:16,280 --> 01:10:17,760
Why did I do that…

859
01:10:17,880 --> 01:10:20,240
I
Mean… I’m not even aware of why I did that.

860
01:10:20,320 --> 01:10:22,040
Shh…

861
01:10:27,200 --> 01:10:28,480
Okay…

862
01:10:28,960 --> 01:10:30,640
whatever we do now,

863
01:10:31,240 --> 01:10:32,800
we can’t turn back time.

864
01:10:32,880 --> 01:10:34,400
The past is already gone.

865
01:10:35,760 --> 01:10:37,760
But we can
still do something about tomorrow.

866
01:10:41,200 --> 01:10:42,960
No negative thinking after all.

867
01:10:45,640 --> 01:10:46,960
I trust you.

868
01:10:51,200 --> 01:10:52,480
I trust you too.

869
01:10:56,240 --> 01:10:57,880
You’re forbidden to me, I know.

870
01:10:59,160 --> 01:11:00,920
But my heart is full of you.

871
01:11:02,080 --> 01:11:03,720
No matter how forbidden you are,

872
01:11:04,400 --> 01:11:08,480
you’re my past, my present, my future now.

873
01:11:09,120 --> 01:11:10,720
I can’t give you up anymore…

874
01:11:20,280 --> 01:11:24,240
If I don’t feel alone in this world, it’s
only because of you.

875
01:11:24,520 --> 01:11:26,720
You’re more real than anyone in my life.

876
01:11:27,800 --> 01:11:29,560
You’re the one in my heart the most…

877
01:11:30,920 --> 01:11:32,440
But how is this possible?

878
01:11:33,080 --> 01:11:35,960
How… You’re forbidden to me.

879
01:11:45,920 --> 01:11:47,440
Why are you looking at me like that?

880
01:11:49,720 --> 01:11:51,080
How am I looking?

881
01:11:53,680 --> 01:11:54,880
Like that…

882
01:11:58,360 --> 01:11:59,760
Because I…

883
01:12:03,120 --> 01:12:04,840
I…
